<a id="top"> </a><h1>Tenure-track Position, Oklahoma State University</h1>
<p>
Philosophy Department, Oklahoma State University Assistant Professor, 
tenure-track, beginning the Fall, 2012 semester. Initial appointment for 
four years. Two-three classes/semester. Some committee work. Salary 
competitive. AOS: either (a) Philosophy of Science, or (b) Contemporary 
Epistemology. AOC: Open. We are searching for a philosopher in the 
Analytic Tradition who can teach Epistemology and Philosophy of Science. 
Ph.D. and some teaching experience required. Application deadline is 
November 28th, 2011. Search will continue until the position is filled. 
This position is subject to available funding.  </p>
